There are always highs and lows in life. It’s the same in nomad life, but it’s unique in that the highs are extremely high and the lows are incredibly low. Sometimes you have to get lost deep in the valley in order to make it to the highest peak of the mountain. Perspective is everything. You learn what really matters and what is insignificant. Sometimes gratitude hits you like a brick wall. Never take anything for granted.
